article.description: Jake Toolson had 25 points as Utah Valley defeated Seattle 77-68 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Toolson scores 25 to lead Utah Valley past Seattle 77-68
article.linkText: Toolson scores 25 to lead Utah Valley past Seattle 77-68
article.story: SEATTLE -- Jake Toolson had 25 points as Utah Valley defeated Seattle 77-68 on Tuesday night. Richard Harward had 14 points and 10 rebounds for Utah Valley (20-8, 9-4 Western Athletic Conference), which won its fourth straight game. Conner Toolson added 11 points. Delante Jones had 16 points for the Redhawks (15-13, 3-10). Morgan Means added 15 points. Terrell Brown had 13 points and eight assists. The Wolverines improve to 2-0 against the Redhawks on the season. Utah Valley defeated Seattle 88-78 on Jan. 12. Both teams take on California Baptist in their next game. Seattle visits the Lancers on Thursday, while Utah Valley remains on the road for its matchup against California Baptist on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
